    <briefdescription>
<para>Synaptic element of a node (axonal bouton or dendritic spine) for the purposes of structural plasticity. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The synaptic elements represent connection points between two neurons that grow according to a homeostatic growth rule. Basically, the dynamics of the number of synaptic elements is driven by the average electrical activity of the neuron (indirectly measured through the Calcium concentration of the node). The probability of two neurons creating a new synapse between them, depends on the number of available synaptic elements of each neuron. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
